  "text": "In mobile network environments, low bandwidth, long round-trip time (RTT) and radio signal variation may aggravate the web loading delay. Since many web content providers are changing their web pages to become mobilefriendly, with sizes between 100 to 200 kbytes, the significance of the low bandwidth, however, is gradually shrinking. In addition, the signal strength is considered to be negligible to TCP downlink performance as long as it is above a threshold [CITATION_1] . Consequently, lots of researchers have claimed that the long RTT of a mobile network is the most significant inhibitor of fast mobile web browsing [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
